    "body": "### Problem\r\n\r\nCurrently, `#offset!` allows clipping the start and end of a node away. It's useful, but it doesn't allow capturing only the block comments' contents.\r\n\r\nExample can be\r\n\r\n```c\r\n// Some C comments\r\n\r\n/**\r\n * Some C block comments\r\n * Foo\r\n * Bar\r\n */\r\n```\r\n\r\nRight now, if I do `#offset!` on the block comment with capture `@node` and `(#offset! @node 0 3 0 -3)`, I will have a range of\r\n```c\r\n * Some C block comments\r\n * Foo\r\n * Bar\r\n```\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nI'd like to ask for a line-based `#offset!`, so that I can remove all the leading `*` inside such block comments, for example, `(#line-offset! 0 3 0 -3)`, and have the resulting capture to be \r\n\r\n```c\r\n// /** is removed, empty line\r\nSome C block comments // <- captured with @node, the leading ` * ` is not captured \r\nFoo                   // <- captured with @node, the leading ` * ` is not captured\r\nBar                   // <- captured with @node, the leading ` * ` is not captured\r\n// <space>*/ is removed, empty line\r\n```",
